# ✅ REAL EXAMPLE: JWT + HTTP‑Only Cookie

## 🧩 Tech Stack

*   Backend: **Node.js + Express**
*   Frontend: **React**
*   Auth: **JWT Access + Refresh Tokens**
*   Cookie: **HTTP‑Only Refresh Token**

***

## ✅ BACKEND

### 1️⃣ Install

```bash
npm install express jsonwebtoken cookie-parser cors
```

***

### 2️⃣ `server.js`

```js
import express from "express";
import jwt from "jsonwebtoken";
import cookieParser from "cookie-parser";
import cors from "cors";

const app = express();
app.use(express.json());
app.use(cookieParser());

app.use(cors({
  origin: "http://localhost:5173",
  credentials: true
}));

const ACCESS_SECRET = "ACCESS_SECRET";
const REFRESH_SECRET = "REFRESH_SECRET";

const users = [{ id: 1, username: "admin", password: "admin" }];

let refreshTokens = [];
```

***

### 🔐 Login (sets cookie)

```js
app.post("/login", (req, res) => {
  const { username, password } = req.body;
  const user = users.find(
    u => u.username === username && u.password === password
  );

  if (!user) return res.sendStatus(401);

  const accessToken = jwt.sign(
    { userId: user.id },
    ACCESS_SECRET,
    { expiresIn: "15m" }
  );

  const refreshToken = jwt.sign(
    { userId: user.id },
    REFRESH_SECRET,
    { expiresIn: "7d" }
  );

  refreshTokens.push(refreshToken);

  res.cookie("refreshToken", refreshToken, {
    httpOnly: true,
    secure: false,     // true in production (HTTPS)
    sameSite: "lax",
    path: "/refresh"
  });

  res.json({ accessToken });
});
```

✅ Cookie stored **automatically by browser**

***

### 🔄 Refresh Token (cookie read by server)

```js
app.post("/refresh", (req, res) => {
  const token = req.cookies.refreshToken;
  if (!token || !refreshTokens.includes(token)) {
    return res.sendStatus(401);
  }

  jwt.verify(token, REFRESH_SECRET, (err, payload) => {
    if (err) return res.sendStatus(403);

    const newAccessToken = jwt.sign(
      { userId: payload.userId },
      ACCESS_SECRET,
      { expiresIn: "15m" }
    );

    res.json({ accessToken: newAccessToken });
  });
});
```

👀 **Notice:** No token in request body  
✅ Browser sends cookie automatically

***

### 🚪 Logout

```js
app.post("/logout", (req, res) => {
  const token = req.cookies.refreshToken;
  refreshTokens = refreshTokens.filter(t => t !== token);

  res.clearCookie("refreshToken", { path: "/refresh" });
  res.sendStatus(204);
});
```

***

# ✅ FRONTEND (React)

## IMPORTANT RULE FOR COOKIES

You **MUST** use:

```js
credentials: "include"
```

Otherwise cookies won’t be sent.

***

## ✅ Login.jsx

```jsx
const login = async () => {
  const res = await fetch("http://localhost:4000/login", {
    method: "POST",
    credentials: "include",
    headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      username: "admin",
      password: "admin"
    })
  });

  const data = await res.json();
  setAccessToken(data.accessToken);
};
```

✅ Cookie saved automatically

***

## ✅ Refresh on App Load (New Tab Support)

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("http://localhost:4000/refresh", {
    method: "POST",
    credentials: "include"
  })
    .then(res => res.json())
    .then(data => setAccessToken(data.accessToken))
    .catch(() => console.log("Not logged in"));
}, []);
```

✅ Works after reload  
✅ Works in new tab  
✅ No JS access to refresh token

***

# ✅ WHAT ACTUALLY HAPPENS (IMPORTANT)

| Step        | Who handles it |
| ----------- | -------------- |
| Save cookie | Browser        |
| Send cookie | Browser        |
| Read cookie | Server         |
| JS access   | ❌ blocked      |

The cookie is **never visible in React code**  
That’s the security win.

***

# ❌ COMMON MISTAKES

❌ Forget `credentials: "include"`  
❌ Use `SameSite=None` without HTTPS  
❌ Try `document.cookie` with HttpOnly  
❌ Store refresh token in localStorage

***

# ✅ Summary

✅ Cookies = browser‑managed storage  
✅ HttpOnly cookies = secure auth  
✅ Automatically sent with every request  
✅ Perfect for refresh tokens  
✅ Used by Google, Microsoft, banks, SSO systems

